    "headerDoc": "STEP 971 — Bipartite Ramsey Numbers: First Lean 4 Formalization\n  藤本伸樹 2026-04-22\n\n  The bipartite Ramsey number b(s, t) is the smallest N such that every\n  2-coloring of the edges of K_{N,N} contains a monochromatic K_{s,s}\n  (symmetric case s = t).\n\n  Known symmetric values:\n    b(2, 2) = 5      (Beineke–Schwenk 1976)\n    b(2, 3) = 9      (Carnielli–Monte Carmelo 2000)\n    b(3, 3) = 17     (Irving 1978 lower; Hattingh–Henning 1998 upper)\n\n  This file formalizes b(2, 2) = 5 in full:\n    * lower bound by explicit 4 × 4 witness via `native_decide`;\n    * upper bound by exhaustive enumeration ov"
  },
